cmd_executor_tool.en:
【Unified Command Execution Tool】
Function: Supports executing shell commands/Shell scripts locally, automatically sets timeout time by command type, terminates execution automatically when timed out (Python native implementation, compatible with common commands and scripts), returns structured multilingual results

【Core Guidelines】
1. Command parameter (command) is required, empty value is not allowed;
2. Timeout parameter (timeout) is optional, if not passed, the default timeout time is automatically matched by command type; if passed, it must be a positive integer (unit: seconds), non-positive integers will automatically use the default value of 15 seconds;
3. Language parameter (lang) is optional, if not passed, the default language in the configuration file is read; if passed, it must be a LanguageEnum enum value (ZH/EN);
4. Mapping rules for command types and default timeout time (priority: user-specified timeout > Shell script command > normal command > global default):
   - Shell script commands (containing .sh, starting with bash / sh ): default 600 seconds;
   - Long-time-consuming commands (yum/apt/docker/scp): 300/300/600/600 seconds respectively;
   - Medium-time-consuming commands (ping/curl): 30 seconds each;
   - Fast commands (ls/pwd/echo/cat/grep): 5/5/5/10/10 seconds respectively;
   - Unmatched commands: global default 15 seconds;
5. The host parameter is a compatibility reserved item, the current version only supports local execution (target fixed as 127.0.0.1), and passing it does not affect the execution logic;
6. Command format requirement: Supports standard shell commands and Shell script paths (e.g."/tmp/run.sh", "bash /root/install.sh"), avoid execution failure caused by illegal commands.

【Enum Class Definition (Must Follow)】
- CommandTimeoutEnum (Command Timeout Enum): LS=5 / PWD=5 / ECHO=5 / CAT=10 / GREP=10 / PING=30 / CURL=30 / YUM=300 / APT=300 / DOCKER=600 / SCP=600 / SHELL_SCRIPT=600 / DEFAULT=15
- LanguageEnum (Language Enum): ZH / EN

【Parameter Details】
- host: Remote host identifier (compatibility reserved item, optional, no actual effect)
- command: Shell command/Shell script to execute (required, standard shell format)
- timeout: Execution timeout time (optional, positive integer, unit: seconds, default matched by command)
- lang: Language type (optional, enum values: ZH/EN, default read from configuration file)

【Return Value Explanation】
- success: Execution result (True=success, False=failure)
- message: Execution info/error prompt (multilingual, such as success, timeout, execution failure, etc.)
- result: Command execution result (returns command output content on success, empty string on failure/timeout)
- target: Execution target (fixed as 127.0.0.1, local execution)
- timeout_used: The actual timeout time used (unit: seconds, convenient for troubleshooting timeout issues)
